ASSIGNMENT 11: WRITE A C PROGRAM TO FIND THE LAST DIGIT OF AN INTEGER a)USING MODULUS b)WITHOUT USING MODULUS.
SOURCE CODE:
#include<stdio.h>
  int main(){
      int n,d1,d2;
      printf("Enter a number: ");
      scanf("%d",&n);
      d1=n%10;
      printf("Using modulus\n");
      printf("Last digit: %d\n",d1);
      d2=n-(n/10)*10;
      printf("Without using modulus\n");
      printf("Last digit: %d",d2);
}

